description:
Exploratory analysis protocol governing the use of Grok (xAI) as a latent&nbsp; 
 manifold probe in support of the FIR-X1 pre-registered study (Zenodo:&nbsp; 
 10.5281/zenodo.20578305). 
 &nbsp; 
 Grok is used as a Grok-as-instrument modality: querying Grok's synthesis of&nbsp; 
 X/Twitter content as a proxy for the latent manifold's retained representation&nbsp; 
 of dormant memes, rather than as an archive retrieval tool. This is a distinct&nbsp; 
 measurement modality from the raw archive data specified in FIR-X1, and all&nbsp; 
 outputs are explicitly labelled exploratory [E-obs]. 
 &nbsp; 
 The protocol is structured as three query tiers: Tier 1 (landscape survey by&nbsp; 
 functional role, producing the FIR-X1 seed list); Tier 2 (role-stability depth&nbsp; 
 probes on individual motif candidates, producing coder training examples);&nbsp; 
 Tier 3 (reactivability, friction, and direct manifold-state probes on&nbsp; 
 shortlisted candidates, producing FIR-X2 design input and theory-level&nbsp; 
 observations). 
 &nbsp; 
 Epistemic status: EXPLORATORY. No output from this protocol constitutes a&nbsp; 
 pre-registered result for FIR-X1. All findings feed forward into the FIR-X1&nbsp; 
 seed list, coder training materials, and the powered replication design&nbsp; 
 (FIR-X2). The confirmatory boundary is the Zenodo timestamp of FIR-X1&nbsp; 
 (10.5281/zenodo.20578305). 
 &nbsp; 
 The protocol includes: full query templates for all three tiers; epistemic&nbsp; 
 boundary rules (E1-E5); a query register template for session-level logging;&nbsp; 
 and a publication plan for exploratory outputs. 
 &nbsp; 
 Programme reference: FIR-OP-001 (Functional Invariant Reachability).

